'''Pneuron Corporation''' provides large [[data integration]] [[software application]]s and technology to the Fortune 5000.<ref name="FB">{{cite web |url=http://www.forbes.com/sites/tomgroenfeldt/2012/07/25/making-disparate-data-meet-business-needs/ |title=Making Disparate Data Meet Business Needs |date=Juy 25, 2012 |author=Tom Groenfeldt |publisher=Forbes |accessdate=February 23, 2013}}</ref><ref name="STM">{{cite web |url=http://www.securitiestechnologymonitor.com/news/pneurons-big-data-no-big-databases-31204-1.html?ET=securitiesindustry:e4020:22409a:&st=email&utm_source=editorial&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=STM_BNA_08302010_082812 |title=Managing Big Data, Without Big Databases |date=August 28, 2012 |author=Tom Steinert-Threlkeld |publisher=Securities Technology Monitor |accessdate=February 23, 2013}}</ref><ref name="BJ">{{cite web |url=http://www.bizjournals.com/boston/blog/mass-high-tech/2011/11/pneuron-fires-up-first-funding-round-at-125m.html |title=Pneuron fires up first funding round at $1.25M |date=November 4, 2011 |author=Rodney H. Brown |publisher=Boston Business Journal |accessdate=February 23, 2013}}</ref> The company's software helps businesses create, deploy and manage new products in [[real-time computing|real-time]] without the need for intermediary [[database]]s, traditional data, [[systems integration]], or incremental hardware.<ref name="STM"/><ref name="TABB">{{cite web |url=http://www.tabbgroup.com/PublicationDetail.aspx?PublicationID=1104&MenuID=44&ParentMenuID=2&PageID=43 |title=Data Agility: Turning a Liability into an Asset |date=June 6, 2012 |author=Miranda Mizen |publisher=Tabb Group |accessdate=February 23, 2013}}</ref> In 2012, Pneuron received a [[Governance, risk management, and compliance|GRC]] Technology Innovation Award, an honor given to companies recognized for providing innovative technology to organizations.<ref name="GRC">{{cite web |url=http://www.grc2020.com/?p=828 |title=2012 GRC Technology Innovation Awards |date=February 8, 2012 |author=Michael Rasmussen |publisher=GRC 20/20 |accessdate=February 23, 2013}}</ref> Pneuron's CEO is Simon Moss.<ref name="WST">{{cite web |url=http://www.wallstreetandtech.com/technology-risk-management/how-to-build-an-effective-enterprise-ris/240005316 |title=How to Build an Effective Enterprise Risk Management System |date=August 10, 2012 |author=Simon Moss |publisher=Wall Street & Technology |accessdate=February 23, 2013}}</ref> Pneuron is headquartered in [[Woburn, Massachusetts]].<ref name="PP">{{Cite press release |url=http://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20120206005865/en/Pneuron-Launches-Business-Driven-Cloud-Platform-Revolutionizes-Enterprise |title=Pneuron Launches Business-Driven Cloud Platform That Revolutionizes Enterprise Application Market |date=February 6, 2012 |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |publisher=Pneuron Corporation |accessdate=March 2, 2013}}</ref>
==History== [[CEO]] Simon Moss and [[Chief operating officer|COO]] Elizabeth Elkins founded Pneuron in 2011.<ref name="FB"/><ref name="BJ"/> Pneuronâ€™s objective is to redefine [[applications architecture|application]] and [[enterprise architecture]] development by reducing time and cost of development, deployment and the maintenance of enterprise applications. <ref name="FB"/><ref name="STM"/><ref name="TABB"/><ref name="WST"/>
In 2012, Pneuron introduced its Pneuron Platform, a [[software suite]] for [[financial services]] firms that distributes key applications and directly sources data systems.<ref name="TABB"/> The platform aids interoperability across [[enterprise systems]] through a dynamic and non-intrusive medium that bypasses traditional systems and hardware costs.<ref name="STM"/><ref name="TABB"/> TABB Research group recognized the Pneuron Platform as an innovation in financial services competitiveness and transparency.
==Partnership== In 2013, Pneuron partnered with global consultancy firm [[PricewaterhouseCoopers]] to help financial firms manage [[big data]].<ref name="ISS">{{cite web |url=http://www.iss-mag.com/regulations-and-compliance/pneuron-and-pwc-tackle-fatca-and-big-data-problems |title=Pneuron and PwC Tackle FATCA and Big Data Problems |date= |author=Chris Kentouris |publisher=International Security Services |accessdate=February 23, 2013}}</ref><ref name="STM"/><ref name="FB"/>
